Uplink info: Each WMM corresponds to a unique DSCP/8021.p value, and the DSCP/8021.p value of each type of WMM cannot be duplicated.The range of the DSCP value is 0-63, the range of the 802.1p value is 0-7.
Downlink info: Each WMM corresponds to a unique DSCP/802.1p value, and the DSCP/802.1p value of each type of WMM cannot be duplicated. The range of the DSCP value is 0-63, the range of the 802.1p value is 0-7.

cannot_get_pvc_info: Operation failed ! Because of getting pvc info failed.
wlanTip: It displays WLAN lists. Click on each row you can see related monitoring and clients information in corresponding display area, and you can also  see the details of WLAN by clicking the title.
apTip: Click on each row in APs lists you can see the monitoring and clients information of this AP in corresponding display area, and you can also see the details of each AP by clicking the title.
clientTip: Click on each row in clients lists, you can see the monitoring information of each client, and you can also get the details of clients by clicking the title.
monitorTip: This module displays statistics information of each ap wlan or client.
systemTip: This is the first level of menu that shows the basic system information. Click here to fold or unfold it.
clusterTip: This area displays the cluster information, you can click here to view the details.
syslogTip: This area displays the AP's syslog information and the configuration of Syslog.
systemTime: This area displays the AP's Date & Time , timezone and NTP server information and  manage  this.
wirelessTip: This is the first level of menu that shows  the information about WirelessLAN. Click here to fold or unfold it.
RFTip: RF Management. Click here to see the details.
RoguAPTip: Rogue AP statistical information. Click here to see the details.
accessTip: This is the first level of menu that shows information about authentication and the related rules. Click here to fold or unfold it.
authTip: Authentication information about local portal. Click here to see the details.
aclTip: ACL rules. Click here to see the details.
FilterTip: Configure user blacklists and whitelists, walled garden.
